    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 credibility factors and the associated evidence base. Despite multiple factors achieving levels below requirements, the team accepted the package on the basis of the hemolysis adequacy claim, which is supported by narratively referenced experimental evidence from the Morrison 2019 in-vitro dataset and the FDA benchmark PIV study. The central adequacy claim is recorded in the package and summarizes the evidentiary basis for acceptance. Residual gaps are acknowledged and flagged for future assessment cycles.",
